Context: George Brown College offers the following marketing programs: 2-year Diploma, 3-year Advanced Diploma, 4-year Degree, and 1-year Graduate Certificate. The college has a "2+2" model that allows students from the 2-year diploma or 3-year advanced diploma to transfer into the degree program. The college is located in downtown Toronto and provides access to industry professionals and potential employers due to its proximity to leading advertising, marketing, and communications agencies. Students learn real-world perspectives from faculty members who continue to work in the industry. The college offers online postgraduate certificate programs for working professionals with a schedule of evenings and weekends. The Entry Advising service helps students match their skills, background, and career goals with program options. Contact information: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca. Online resources include a social media hub and sign up for application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more.
